The paper deals with data-detection and precoding algorithms for wireless systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of orthogonal frequency-division multiplexing (OFDM) or single-carrier frequency-division multiple access (SC-FDMA) also suggests a possible fit in the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. The paper also deals with massive multi-user (MU) multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which are studied in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
